caption: Simple menu, good food, attentive staff. The bread, especially the crust is heavenly.
I tried to call in a million times and no answer terrible service!!

If you visit Bethesda in Maryland, the first thing to do is to have a meal at Medium Rare restaurant. This is my second visit to this restaurant. The taste of the food stay in your memory waiting for the next visit. They bring the food in two parts, after you finish the first dish they surrprise you with  refill. The dish has the steak and fried potatoes. You need 1:15:00 min to enjoy finishing your meal. You can park on the road and pay $2 per hour.
Still great steak dinner at a great price you can't miss there.

Price fix, good value, good wine. Tasty desserts. You get bread, 2 servings of steak and fries and a green salad. The fries were a bit salty and the meat a bit overcooked, but the meat was my fault since I asked for medium, not medium rare. The dessert was great, as was the wine. Screw cap, but good. I'm very surprised that they did not have a cocktail menu. I want to like the place. It's unique, but honestly not good enough for me to return. It IS a good value. Lots of food. We each had steak, apple pie and we split the wine. $65 pre tip, $80 post tip. The bread was a bit crusty. The staff writes on the table cloth. Not fancy. FYI they have an off menu vegetarian portabello mushroom cap entree.
Steak & frites are delicious and reasonable priced.

I love this restaurant so much! Amazing food, amazing owner, and amazing idea of a steak frites restaurant in the DC area!  I commend them for such an amazing job in how they’ve handled the Covid situation, as well as their outside dining experience!  They provide a tent with heated air that comes from a Mr heat machine, and though the tables maybe could be a bit further apart, I felt relatively safe with the plants in between us all!
Medium Rate is my go to for Steak and Fries. Service is superb! But I always enjoy the cut of meat and preparation. It simply tastes good! Enjoy!
It was great food
Surely a spot worth visiting, the food is awesome and well prepared, the rates are fair and it is constantly neat in here. Keep up the good work.
Very nice and clean family friendly staff are friendly food service great beautiful place
Wait staff with excellent. Steak and fries was very l good. I  would go again after covid-19 if it ever ends.
Amazing food! I love this restaurant it's high quality meat with an amazing gravy

It’s crazy how one really bad experience can ruin all the good ones. My husband loves this place so much he ordered some take-out. As he was checking his food to make sure everything was correct, “Vanessa”, a manager, approaches him saying “What are you doing? Is that your food??” Completely offending my husband who was handed the bag by another staff member. She treated him as if he were some random person scavenging for food. She never greeted him or asked if he was being assisted. She immediately just treated him like trash. This place will never see our family or our employees here EVER AGAIN!!!

Don’t know what the hype is all about? Went for brunch today.  Had to ask for drinks 3 times before they were finally brought.  Fruit salad, melons was under ripe and lacked flavor.  Both our Eggs Benedict was cold, had to send back.  2nd time was very salty.  Was never checked on during the meal.  Empty glasses sat and we had to ask for refills (coffee and water).  Was there for my birthday, I regret picking this restaurant to celebrate a rare kid free lunch.
Simple one menu. Good salad, excellent meat cooked as asked, good frites. Very good service and not expensive.
Great service. Great location. Best french toast I have ever had! And the best bottomless brunch deal you can get in the DMV.
Great food and service
Didn't like the atmosphere the food was cold the service was terrible wouldn't recommend this restaurant to no one

Excellent 👌,, love the food perfectly served . If I could have one complaint, I loved the fried potatoes but a bit heavy on the salt still that's a matter of personal tastes 😅. There beef was correctly prepared to exactly the setting ordered. I had a Medium rare and my partner a Medium  steak  they were exact  . BRAVO PEOPLE. So many restaurants can't figure that out. The service was well times in all a very pleasant experience.
Love their menu! Great steak, salad, fries ans sourdough bread for only $25. Add a glass of wine and sit outside on the sidewalk for an almost French experience :)
Went there for brunch. Server was attentive and good, only a bit slow. Food portions were ok. 4 stars, not 5, because they forgot about my coffee + not much to choose from during brunch.

Medium rare restaurant is a great place for a set menu type of place, my family and I go there all the time. The steak and the fries were great (ordered it medium rare) the salad is made with Dijon mustard which I love. The “secret” sauce of the stake is to die for. The only thing I will recommend is sometimes the steak came kind of cold, so ask you server from the beginning to make sure it hot. Oh and it is pet friendly at the patio if you have a dog!
Great food and safe practises during covid19
Food was really good!!  Salad and steak was amazing!  I only wished they had more selections on the sauce/gravy.  But overall it was very delicious!

My family and I decided to have dinner here tonight. There were five of us and we sat inside. The food was good, can’t complain about that and the salad  was very tasty  BUT my beef ( excuse the pun) is the cost for the alcohol. Three in our party got 2 drinks that cost roughly $12.50 each...ok not a big deal for Bethesda . Two of us shared a carafe of Sangria. The cost of this carafe was $50 . I have never spent that much on a carafe of Sangria. NEVR AGAIN
I love Medium Rare! The food is amazing, the staff is lovely, and I’m happy to lick the sauce ladle clean.

Came and got brunch on the patio for the first time since things have been reopening. Richard H provided excellent service! He knew it was about to rain and offered us inside seating. Make sure to ask for him when you come in, you won't be disappointed.  We ordered steak and eggs. The steak was cooked and seasoned perfectly. The special sauce was amazing as well. Overall excellent experience 10/10 would recommend.
Bad customer service, no email contact on website.
I’ve eaten at your restaurant several times but you lost my business because you only cook meat medium for carry out.

An online paid order was placed at 5pm for 7:10pm pickup.  after waiting on a line to check in for an hour from 7pm to 8pm, i'm told its going to be another 30-40 minutes.  Absolutely unacceptable.  Was forced to wait in a crowd to be told my food is over 1.5 hours late.  AVOID LIKE THE PLAGUE DURING THIS CONTACT-LESS PICKUP TIME  They are completely disorganized and unable to handle organizing a prepaid order pickup

Salad is delicious, gravy is sinful and fries are irresistible. But the meat itself has dropped in quality. Stringy, chewy, tougher cheap grade. And serving stale bread is just pathetic. Just shameless...  Plate has a $9 value and a $25 pricetag.

Okay Medium Rare was delicious. I wanted to treat myself to a good meal and knew I wanted some good meat. Well I wasn’t disappointed. MR has a set menu: bread, salad, steak and fries. I was skeptical about how the sauce was gonna taste (I am from the South) but it was satisfactory. You get a second helping of steak and fried (hence my dessert to go). Dessert was sub-par: key lime pie. Not a true pie (it was a whipped consistency) and the cookie crunch pearls added nothing.

Great customer service. My grandmother heard about the free meals for seniors during the pandemic and was so excited to get hers. When it didnt come I contacted the restaurant and they redelivered it again the next night. They really went above and beyond and were super nice. She said it was the most delicious meal. I cant wait to dine in this establishment as I'm sure it is an A+ facility.

As a widowed senior citizens I was just the recipient of a delicious, free dinner, delivered to my apartment door.   What a fabulous treat!   The whole delicious meal, seconds and all.   Thank you so much!!   Hope to be back in the restaurant very soon.   I promised my daughter a birthday dinner there but I had to back out because I am confined to my apartment.

Medium Rare just delivered dinner for my husband and I because we are high risk for going out during the virus pandemic. The food was delicious and the gesture was extraordinarily kind. We have eaten in the restaurant a number of times and we would recommend it highly.
Amazing place!! The sauce is the secret.
This place is amazing!!  Steak was cooked perfectly, the fries were nice and crispy and the apple pie is to die for!  Go try it out.
Love this place  Great steak
Food was solid, many families celebrating, big portions.
Weird not having a selection of steaks for it to be a steakhouse.
Awesome food and everything it was awesome I already said that but it’s AWESOME

Been to this location three or four times in the past six months, and service is always on point. Food comes out quickly (but you'll never feel rushed), and it's never shy of delicious. This location is becoming an easy and frequent date night option for us.
Food and service were excellent
Never had it before, so wanted to try it. Honestly, if you love steak and fries. This is the place for you. Not a whole lot of choices. But again if you love steak and fries, it was really good.
The gravy is to die for!

The concept of this place is really awesome. Simple, easy to bring guests. Almost no thinking at all about what to order! I just wish their "famous" gravy tasted better. Don't really understand why anyone would think it's great gravy. Next time, I'll be nixing it altogether.
This place follows the maxim of do one thing and do it well.  Great service, good food, and a good value. Our server even got us a bottle of wine off menu.  Will be back!
Brunch is just as amazing as their normal food. Highly recommend for any meal.

I definitely recommend this restaurant.  It's a prefix menu but they do what they do very well. Key lime was excellent and for dessert. Almost a mousse like consistency. Chocolate cake was excellent and decadent. Hot fudge Sunday was well over the top.  The steak was tender. Almost didn't need the second helping. Great portions for the price.
Really good brunch menu but meal portion isn't worth the price.
I certainly like their food and customer service, awesome area nearby to where I live. The workers are always super nice. Will come back again.
Good steak although that is all they have.
If you only do one thing you better do it well, and they do make a very good steak and fries.

We met with friends at this restaurant for lunch. we heard about this place from quite a few people.  Well, it was a winning. The crew were very polite and we had a great feeling. The food was just great. We had a great time and we will visit this place again. Highly recommended.

A full steak dinner in Bethesda for $24?!  Salad, two servings of steak and fries, good bread.  I get the vegetarian option (not listed on the menu but always available), which is grilled portabello mushrooms, sliced thin, with the same type of red sauce as the steaks.  Beverages and desserts are extra. The wines by the glass are well chosen and cost around 12-15 dollars.  Not cheap, but good value for the quality.  Good hospitality, but can be a bit loud.  Outside (in season) is less noisy.

Great food, though a vegan selection would be nice.  Too noisy when full, made worse by the nature of the space and music played too loudly.  The result of the loud music is everyone speaks more loudly.  When we left after brunch, we couldn't conduct a conversation across the table.
Friendly staff, great price! Love their bread’s butter. Unlike other restaurant, They played a recorded French lesson in the restroom so you can learn some French sentences/ word while in it .
Fixed menu but right in my wheelhouse!
Good service.
Great food and service at this location, but unfortunately the service at their Arlington Virginia is abysmal!!!
The sauce was just fine, but the steak and fries were really good. And the portion was more than I was expecting!
Amazing food, great price
Best steak restaurant in all of Maryland and it's not even close. The food and service is amazing every single time I go there without fail. Great for a special occasion or just a date night.
Tasty food .. good atmosphere
The Benedict from brunch is way too salty. The dinner was good.
Great service elevates the food and entire experience. Medium Rare delivered just that
Decent atmosphere. Comes with additional portion. Reasonable price.
A little pricey for what the amount of food you receive buy delicious!
A Prix fixe restaurant with phenomenal offerings. Highly recommended on the condition that you are okay with the one selection on offer.
Excellent Steak, Service and Fixed Price
Extremely happy with this restaurant. The service was excellent. And the food was very good. Would highly recommend this to other people and planning to go back again.

Interesting concept with a prefixe menu of bread, salad, steak and fries. That's it..unless you want a portabello mushroom in lieu of steak. The bread, salad and fries were great and there's a nice selection of drinks. The steak was a cut I'm not familiar with. Rather thin but tender and flavorful.

Fri evening 8 pm called ahead to ask about current wait. Man says 'Come on in, we have tables.' Showed up at door 8 min later, hostess says 35 min wait. Worse, she has a 'so, deal with it' attitude. Worked out great, we walked half a block to Positano, had a great time there...

Dinner menu is more of announcement what's being served that night. It's delicious, staff attentive, and great price.
Been going here for years. Not just this location but the one in DC.  The catch is that it is a set meal. You just pick which of 2salad dressings, atmosphere laid back, casual family friendly
Good simple food.  Enthusiastic services at resonable prices.
I like the idea of a fixed menu. No need to wonder about what to eat besides dessert and drinks. Would easily reccomend and already have. Great spot, hidden gem.
Great experience.  Only steak and fries on the menu but they do a fantastic job.  Love that they bring out half your meal, then the other half comes out hot 15 minutes later.
Best steak ever

Five stars across the board. Food, service, and price are all incredible. The outdoor seating during a nice day is an especially lovely touch. The menu is simple, no fuss; just tell them how you like your steak cooked and you're good to go!  First comes the bread which puts most other crusty bread to shame. It's delicious with a solid crunch in every bight. Next, a salad that is of surprising quality for a place you come mostly for steak. It's simple, elegant, and deliciously tender which offers a delightful contrast from the crunchy bread. Last, the steak and fries. The steak is tender and juicy and comes with their renowned secret steak sauce that's good enough to drink. The fries are similar to McDonald's golden treasures and pair wonderfully wilh the steak and help soak up the juices. Just when you think it's done, round two of steak and fries comes out, complete with more steak sauce.  Pro tip: You can ask for more bread while you have your steak to take full advantage of soaking up that steak sauce.
Great place to spend some time in a nice atmosphere. They have only one dish on the menu, but the meat is really good and the sauce is delicious. They only need to add a vegetarian dish.
Place was a different experience. It had a good atmosphere to meet with friends.
The fries are addictive! The drinks were awesome! The steak is definitely amazing. I went for brunch and I really enjoyed myself.
Awedome food, great service

$22.95 gets you a salad and 12 oz of steak and fries. Pretty good deal. The steak was tasty and tender. The service was good. The desserts are extra ($9 each) which was not 100% clear on the menu. Parking can be an issue. There are parking meters on the street and a parking garage nearby. However, the parking garage closes at 10 pm on Fridays and does not open again until Monday. So do not leave it in there past 10 pm on Friday night or you will have to call their emergency number and deal with that.
Great restaurant with a good food.
Excellent  food excellent service
Great food at a great price
Always a great time, simple yet yummy menu, you know exactly what you come for, don't forget to ask for extra steak sauce
the most amazing secret steak sauce I have ever had. I have tried to recreate it, but their sauce just can't be beat!
Awesome food and great drinks and exceptional quality staff and great waiter service and I'll definitely will be back

When i went here i had the time of my life. Now i only ordered the medium rare steak but i would expect the taste of all the other steaks to be the same. THE SAUCE IS TO DIE FOR!! Their sauce is what this place is known for and boy let me tell you its true the sauce is amazing it is a must try. Waiters and waitresses are extremely polite and high mannered. This place should be one of the first things you go to in bethesda. I just want to thank medium rare for this one of a kind experience.

Always delicious. Brunch comes with all you can drink or a la carte now- I love the option since my mom and Granny don't want anything to drink anyway. The secret sauce they serve with the steak- ugh- my mouth is watering just thinking about it. I always get the French toast, it's so crunchy and perfect!!
If you haven't been to a Medium Rare, just go now. You will get a salad and then a steak and fries covered in delicious. It's awesome, and straight forward and for a great price.
Absolutely loved it here!!! The service was awesome. Our waiter was so kind. 10/10 recommend!

Excellent place for dinner. Fixed menu of steak and fries. The steak is always perfect! They bread and salad dressing are delicious as well! Service was excellent. It was a bit loud in the restaurant.

Simple, but they nail it.
High recommended for Brunch. The bottomless mimosas are amazing - they keep your glass full!  Also great for groups - as long as you have a reservation.
steik was  very thin and dry.

Wow this brunch was amazing. I couldn't quite finish my Eggs Benedict and I ended up taking it home to eat a few hours later. It was THAT good. Whatever is in the special sauce is addicting. Great deal to have bottomless drinks and then an starter and entree for less than $30. Perfect for a Saturday brunch.
Great atmosphere, one item on the menu, food severed to perfection

Okay, but not the great deal we had remembered.  The steak is okay, not a fabulous cut.  Taste and texture varied from one serving to the next.  If you are going for volume (additional servings) it might be good.  If you really want a great steak frites, you're better served going elsewhere.  The atmosphere is okay, nothing special.  Service was mediocre.  Dinner for three was $86 before tip with only one glass of wine total.

Nice brunch. Even though it is fixed menu options are good and food is good. One downside is while they are kid friendly there is no kids menu or kids portion sizes. So if taking kids price can get expensive. 27.99 per kid for brunch is a bit much

Pros: - Great atmosphere - Waiter was good - Fries were great - Steak was medium rare  Cons (but sort of pro because it was funny): We were trying to figure out the dressing on the salad. I bet $5 that it was Caesar dressing. We asked one of the workers what type of dressing it was and she said, "I dunno" and left to stand in a corner. I thought that maybe she would go find out and get back to us, but we never heard from her again. It was dijon vinaigrette and I lost the bet.  Would we go back here? I dunno.
We ate here for the first time & brought our 2yr old after reading other reviews. Surprisingly a great family option. Menu is very simple but the food & service were very good.

I'm probably in between a 4 and a 5. I only go to Medium Rare for brunch and even though their price has gone up over the years I still think it's the best value. The steak and eggs is definitely the best entree in my opinion since you get the steak and fries plus eggs cooked your way. Steak is nothing special, doesn't stand out but certainly not bad, but the sauce for the steak is tasty.  Out of the starters I think the green salad is the best, it's a good size and is very tasty. When you add in the bottomless coffee and mimosas it is easily worth the of price.
Don't underestimate the pre fixed course food. Good service n decent food!

Consistently a poor experience. Every time I come here with friends or family I order medium rare yet the steak I receive is a dry and tasteless medium. At this point I've given up and expect a poor experience automatically. I can't recommend this place to anyone.

They only do one set dinner option (well, two if you consider the vegetarian option) and they do it well. This is NOT a high end steakhouse. If you are wanting that experience, go somewhere else. This is Steak Frites American style with an above average salad and amazing bread.  Staff were friendly and fun. Drinks were alcoholic. And good.

Best to go on a weeknight. Don't let the simplicity fool you.

Dinner consists of salad, bread, beef, and fries; Simple but delicious. Try their warm spiked cider. It's perfect for this cold weather.  Make sure you go on an empty stomach because the server brings you seconds.

Excellent fries and dessert (I had key lime pie). First round of steak was a little thin, gray, and flavorless except for the nice addition of gravy. Second round of steak had better flavor,  texture, and char. Service was mostly very good, friendly and quick, but forgot things we ordered a couple of times. I would come back for the fries and dessert, hands down. And, I wish they had a NY strip night once a week or something.
It was pretty good but steak came out over cooked first order and salad was warm. I also found it odd that the entree was served in two parts. The steak and fries were good though.

This is one of my go to places for date night just about any day of the week. The steak is perfect every time and it should be since it's all they serve!  Recently found out they do have a vegetarian option, but I can't speak to how that is. One of my favorite places to go in the area.

Our go-to weekday spot for some good steak!  We come here as a family for dinner once a week since my young daughter is on a steak kick these days.  Food is consistent, and a great deal at $22 per person for steak, well seasoned and crispy fries, salad, and fresh bread that has incredibly crisp crust.  There is only 1 item on the menu, so if you don’t enjoy the lean type of hanger steak they serve here, this is not the restaurant for you.  I think it’s the best value steak frites I’m Bethesda.  The deserts are hit or miss.  If you like humongous, sweet cakes like those served at The Cheecake Factory, you will enjoy all the cakes and the sundae here.  If you’re looking for a smaller sized dessert with more tartness, go for the key lime pie.  Wine list is limited but has a good selection with good prices.
Been there few times and it’s fantastic.

An unexpected concept for a restaurant. They serve ONE MEAL: dinner salad, culotte cut of steak with a special sauce topping, and seasoned fries, all for (currently) $22.95. Decent beer selection as well as several dessert options (at additional charge). Six of us ate for about $200 with tip.  The food was delicious, the waitstaff helpful and friendly, and the environment casual without being raucous. The dining space is small, so call ahead of make a reservation (though we were able to get our table on Saturday night at 1830 with no problem).  They do have a weekend brunch, but I haven't tried that, so can't comment.  This is a clever addition to the multitude of Bethesda dining options. Great option for someone who wants a quick, easy, delicious meal.

Food is sub par and service was terrible. The main menu of the item was completely non distinctive. The main menu item is also named after a European dish but it is prepared nothing in the least white that dish

The service at this steak frites joint is just outstanding. The staff worked together, had an amazing rapport with each other, and were the example of awesome!  They do the thing they do the thing they do to excellence. The meat is on point, the bar service is awesome, and the key lime pie is off the hook.  Don't walk in expecting it to be what it's not. It's a steak frites joint, and they do it to perfection! Just wish they had cable....

Vanessa! You’re great! You run such a fun happy, energetic environment! Thank you for being such a great host to my friends and I! Hands down the best $25 Bucks i’ve spent in a long time! Thank you and I will definitely see you soon!!!!!!😊👌🏼

This spot has been on my radar for quite awhile and I have heard nothing but stellar reviews. My wife and I live in the area so on Wednesday night we decided to finally give it a shot.  It was a friendly neighboor environment from the moment we were greeted at the door. Suraj was our server and he couldn't have been more accommodating.  I wasnt sure about the secret sauce at first so I requested to have it come on the side. However, let me say. Not necessary!  My wife and I both basically licked the plate clean.  If you use some of that outstanding bread to sop up the remaining sauce on the plate, your life will be better because of it.  So here's the thing though.  The meal comes with a second helping!  Can you beleive that?!  It caught us completely by surprise and almost rendered me incapable of ordering desert.  Of course we had to though.  My wife wanted key lime pie so we split a slice.  It may have been the best key lime pie I've ever had but by this point there was nothing shocking about that.  Wonderful experience.  Excellent staff.  We will be back for sure!

I think I went to this restaurant with my family with a bit of high expectation and left disappointed. The service was good, the main issues were the salad dressing and the on the steak sauce. There was nothing special about them and tasted very "cheap", specially the steak sauce. At very least the steak sauce should have been ptional. The meal was also not kid friendly at all. Apart from the sauce issue, the steak is seasoned with blackpeper, not very kid friendly (and there is no other option for kids).
Love the food and price. This location had/has a rude hostess which is unfortunate
Service is great but the steak is mediocre and so are the portions.  I can see why there is a second serving.
Reasonable fix price menu.  They only serve one thing, but the steak is delicious.

This is a great place with a wonderful staff. The vibe is awesome!! It's a must visit.
Good food and attentive service. Superb bread and I liked the steak better without the secret sauce.

In case you haven't guessed from the name, Medium Rare is a restaurant specializing in steak. In fact, they're so specialized that they only have one item on the dinner menu - steak and frites! Having tried both their brunch (bottomless mimosas) and dinner (two servings of steak!), I honestly have to say that it is worth the price tag. Tasty food aside, servers are friendly and helpful, and the restaurant has a light-hearted vibe to it. It gets crowded during dinner so if you prefer a more relaxing experience try their brunch for sure!
How do they dare and call this meat shavings steaks.  Cold, rubbery and no flavor. It is cheap but you get what you pay for
Love the fixed menu, love the French voice over in the bathroom!!
Brunch is not worth the price. Service was inattentive.

First of all, I lovvvvve a good brunch and I was extremely impressed with their steak and eggs. The poached egg and steak I had were mouth watering. Excellent food, excellent service and a relaxed environment(not overwhelmingly loud inside which is also attractive). The management staff is incredibly accommodating and attentive. I haven't had the opportunity to try their dinner menu yet however I'll definitely be returning soon.

I can't rate this restaurant highly enough. The bread is amazing- the best outside of Paris. The salad with mustard vinaigrette is incredible and the entree' is to die for- perfectly cooked culotte steak, beautifully seared on the outside and cooked perfectly inside with that divine sauce and the best french fries I've ever had--- every time.

I was extremely pleased with  Medium Rare. I went for Brunch with a friend.  I was very amazed with their service, food, prices, and environment.  The service was great. we were immediately greeted us with a smile. Our main server was very attentive, frequently refilling our waters and mimosas. He did a great job of explaining the menu and was even kind enough to let me taste the vegetarian option- mushrooms- to help me decide if I wanted to try the streak or go vegetarian for that meal. Other severs frequently stopped by to check on our table and were very friendly.  The food was amazing. The fruit was fresh. I tried to vegetarian option- portabella mushroom. It was very delicious, not undercooked and came with a very flavorful red sauce. I also tried the steak and eggs. I was happy to see my eggs were cooked exactly how I had asked, this doesn't happen often during brunch since most places are very busy so it was a nice surprise. I also tried the eggs Benedict. I have never had a better benedict. Instead of the traditional ham, the plate came with a perfect blend of protabella mushrooms and steak in a heavy thick gravy type sauce. Talk about an explosion of flavors! I cant express enough how good the food was.  It also came out warm and I did not have to wait a long time to get the meal.  The prices were also great. We had bottomless brunch and food for about $25. This is a steal compared to other brunch spots in Bethesda. And they arent stingy on the mimosas either, the server was very attentive to bring out refills whenever he saw the glass just below half full.  The environment was also lovely. We sat outside, I had a nice view, there wasn't that much foot traffic that would make one feel uncomfortable.  Overall it was a great experience. I would rate Medium Rare a 10 and would recommend it to everyone!
Food and atmosphere where both great. The staff are friendly and hospitable. Limited choices for food and drinks, however what they do make they are vary good at.

I was very pleased with Medium rares brunch.  With my friend we tired to Benedict and the steak and eggs.  Both meals were absolutely amazing. I am happy with the table service.  I had three different servers come to refill water, mimosas, and bread. the food also came fast, hot and delicious, just like Channing Tatum. I also enjoyed the decor, the environment is great with friendly staff and attentive managers like Paulos. I will definitely let be coming back!
good salad, fun idea but wouldn't go back
Close to the real thing

First of all, the facade outside and the name alone makes you feel as if you are in for a fine dining experience. We went to Medium Rare for dinner, and were massively disappointed. The atmosphere was crowded and loud, with poor lighting and zero privacy.  Also, did I mention that the table cloths were PAPER. Clearly no expense was spared. Our bill (for two) was $60, including a $6 coke. You would think they could find the money to splurge and purchase something other than paper tablecloths.  The food did arrive promptly, and the waitress was helpful enough. However, the water was lukewarm, and the bread and salad (dressed mere hours before) were underwhelming.When it comes to the main course, the steak had the taste and texture of a cheap cut and the shoestring french fries (ore-ida, by taste) were reminiscent of an after-school meal. Our second helping (?) was not prepared correctly, but it was promptly fixed and then served... out of a cookie sheet. For those who enjoy a spectacle, please take note that anniversaries and birthdays are punis-- celebrated with sparklers which stink up the entire restaurant moments after ignition. Finally, to top off the entire evening, we were presented with our check, and two pieces of DUBBLE BUBBLE BRAND BUBBLE GUM?? Seriously, who serves rock hard bubble gum from the 80's in place of an after dinner mint or chocolate? The entire experience was bizzare. The two stars in this review are for the somewhat friendly (if busy) staff, and the cleanliness of the location.

This was my first time at Medium Rare. I was visiting from St.Louis and never heard of this type of menu. The food was really good. We all left very full and very satisfied. It was hard to keep the kids away from the bubble gum. We were there for my birthday and my celebratory hot fudge sundae was wonderful.
Food is fun and simple and really tasty.
Delicious!!

I had my first experience at Medium Rare tonight and was pleasantly surprised. The food was very satisfactory and well priced. Service was attentive and the second helping was a nice bonus! The only drawback was the price of their beers which were exorbitant. We will definitely be returning!
Disappointing

The place is just getting up and running, but it's becoming more and more popular, and the staff is on the ball. You can't beat the value; $20 dinner with their perfectly-cooked steak with their great mushroom sauce, and fries; and bottomless mimosas/poinsettias are included for brunch.
Attentive service, good location in Bethesda, and -- most important -- delicious food.  Steak was done right, and fries were on point.  Great coffee, too.

If you want an unpretentious restaurant that serves just steaks and potatoes, this is the right place for you. Medium Rare suits its name properly with thin slices of quality sirloin, tender and juicy to satisfy your cravings for meat. The set menu is straight forward and almost redundant to read since there is no other meats or seafoods to choose from. Their side of skinny fries makes for good snacks but be sure not to pass on the desserts. Both key lime pie and chocolate sundae  rivals any desserts offered in this culinarily rich neighborhood. What makes a perfect evening for us as we sat outside on a beautiful Bethesda evening was the pleasant waiter. Having served many years at their original Cleveland Park location, he is well trained and proud to cater us well past the closing hour.
Not a good location.  Our waiter was quite rude and the place was incredibly noisy. We left before our food arrived. Check out the other location in DC instead.
Prix fixe menu only, but if you like steak, fries, and salad then it is great food for the price

This particular Medium Rare tends to be louder inside than the other two in DC. I personally enjoy the one in Eastern Market/Capital Hill best but it's a far hike from Montgomery County, MD. The food is still delicious each time and I have only been disappointed once. Was unaware brunch service provided one serving as opposed to the usual two and the waiter didn't tell us ahead of time. We likely would have come back at a later time if informed.
If you want to gulp your meal and be out of there in under an hour,.then this is your place.  Certainly not my idea of a relaxing experience!
Loved the service and the food was excellent!
A welcome addition to the Bethesda scene. Medium Rare comes with its reputation of good meals and affordable brunch which includes bottomless drinks. Great staff and outdoor seating.
I have to say this was not the best steak I have tasted however it was nice that they served it in two portions
A great brunch place, with bottomless mimosas/etc and extremely attentive staff. I've been a fan of Medium Rare in Cleveland Park for years and am thrilled to now how one within walking distance!
Great service, Great Food
Friendly staff and good food!!!

I have seen Medium Rare in Cleveland Park many times but never tried it.  The menu is limited.  You get bread, salad, steak and fries for $20 per person.  They serve the steak and fries twice so the food is hot.  The bread was very good.  The steak is good enough but not great.  Service is very friendly.  That is the area it earned the fourth star.  For the price, it is very good.
Excellent meet and very good service.
As good as the other Medium Rares
Excellent food!
Great service and food.
